In this article, President Trump discusses the need to solve the healthcare situation in the US, stating that Obamacare is a "total disaster" and is "melting down". He mentions the significant rate increases in Alaska and Arizona and expresses his desire to find a solution. He invited several individuals to discuss the issue and states that they are getting close to a resolution. However, he emphasizes that healthcare cannot be based on Obamacare. He also mentions that critics have been making judgments about the bill without fully understanding it. The President then asks the press to leave and expresses his appreciation for their presence. When asked about his thoughts on the Senate bill, he responds by saying that he believes it will be great.